text_blocks.snippet: Tina Turner passed away on May 24, 2023, at the age of 83.
Turner was a versatile entertainer who excelled in various creative roles throughout her 60-year career.

table: Powerful, gritty vocals with a contralto/mezzo-soprano range. Mastered rock, soul, R&B, and pop genres.
Global Icon: Dubbed the "Queen of Rock 'n' Roll"; winner of 12 Grammy Awards.
Known for high-energy, "quicksilver" stage movement and iconic dance routines.
Elite: Influenced generations of performers, including Mick Jagger and Beyoncé.
Composed original material, including the hit "Nutbush City Limits".
Highly Skilled: Wrote nine out of ten songs on the 1972 album Feel Good.
Award-Winning: Won an NAACP Image Award for her role in Mad Max Beyond Thunderdome.
Bestseller: Her autobiography I, Tina was a bestseller and adapted into a major biopic.

text_blocks.snippet: Note on Instruments: While a prolific musician and bandleader, Turner did not typically play instruments on stage, focusing her performance on vocals and dance.
At the time of her death, Tina Turner resided in Küsnacht, Switzerland.

list.snippet: City/State: Küsnacht (a municipality in the district of Meilen), near Zurich.

Details: She lived at Villa Algonquin, a lakefront estate overlooking Lake Zurich, where she had been a resident since 1994. She relinquished her U.S. citizenship in 2013 to become a permanent Swiss citizen.
